First Read: 03-Feb-26
HB368 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to Randolph County; to provide for staggered
4 terms for members of the county commission.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
6 Section 1. Effective for the general election in 2028,
7 the members of the Randolph County Commission representing
8 Districts 1, 3, and 5 shall be elected for terms of two years
9 and the other members shall be elected for terms of four
10 years. Thereafter, at the general election preceding the
11 expiration of the term of any member of the commission, any
12 successor shall be elected for a term of four years.
13 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
14 1, 2026.
